Since release 1.5, you can embed Flash content or movies (Quicktime or Windows Media) into a page as easily as you can an image: 

Not as easily in practice because the pop-up window activated through the editor doesn't list the attachments that are not pictures. It needs to be upgraded to fetch as well .swf, .mov, .wmf...

After entering this code using the Wiki Markup editor:
{code}
{section}
{column:width=50%}
{panel:title=Test Space|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#6699cc|bgColor=#cee7ff}
Blah blah 1
{panel}
{panel:title=Hot Topics|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#FF9900|bgColor=#FFFFCC}
Blah blah 2
{panel}
{recently-updated}
{column}
{column}
{panel:title=Topic Groups|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#d0d9bd|bgColor=#f5f7f1}
Blah blah 3
{panel}
{column}
{section}
{code}

If you just edit it using the Rich Text editor, it then becomes:

{code}
{section}{column:width=50%}
{panel:title=Test Space|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#6699cc|bgColor=#cee7ff}
Blah blah 1
{panel}
{panel:title=Hot Topics|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#FF9900|bgColor=#FFFFCC}
Blah blah 2
{panel}{recently-updated}{recently-updated}{column}{column}
{panel:title=Topic Groups|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#d0d9bd|bgColor=#f5f7f1}
Blah blah 3
{panel}{column}{section}
{code}

The Rich Text editor should not remove Carriage Returns.
It should not duplicate the {recently-updated} instruction.

{noformat}
If you type in an explicit backslash (using the HTML entity - &#092;) in wiki markup, then switch to WYSIWYG mode, the backslash appears fine, but upon conversion back to wiki markup mode, the backslash is no longer escaped (and is the normal \ character).
{noformat}

Seems to be 2 types of user retrieved - is this a bug or intentional?

{code}
    public boolean isPermitted()
    {
        // This page is only permitted if the user to whom the attachments belong is allowed to attach
        // files.
        User user = getRemoteUser();
        User whyDoWeHave2Users = getUser();
        return GeneralUtil.isSuperUser(whyDoWeHave2Users) ||
                (permissionManager.hasPermission(SpacePermission.USE_CONFLUENCE_PERMISSION, null, user, user.getGroups()) &&
                permissionManager.hasPermission(attachmentPermissionTypes, null, whyDoWeHave2Users));
    }
{code}

